text: Palestine at the Olympics is a history which includes 5 games in 5 countries and 10+ athletes.SportsReference.com (SR/Olympics), "Palestine" ; retrieved 2012-7-27. Since 1996, Palestine (PLE) has contributed to the growth of the "Olympic Movement".Olympics.org, "Factsheet: The Olympic Movement"; retrieved 2012-7-27. ==History== Palestine has been at the Summer Olympics since 1996. Since 1986 Palestine is part of the Olympic Council of Asia (OCA). (Israel is a member of the European Olympic Committee.) Palestine has not won any Olympic medals. ==Related pages== * List of IOC country codes ==References== ==Other websites== * Palestine profile at London2012.com Category:Palestinian culture Category:Nations at the Olympics
